{"word":"ἐπάνειμι","slug":"ἐπάνειμι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπάνειμι</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:εἶμι'><el>εἶμι</el></a>, <i>ibo</i>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>used as <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> of <el>ἐπ-ανέρχομαι</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to go back, return</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>:—in writing or speaking, <i>to return</i> to a point, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <i>to recapitulate</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}